## Intersectionality and Race

The gender pay gap is not uniform across all women. Women of color face larger pay gaps compared to white women, with Black, Native American, and Latina women experiencing significantly lower earnings relative to white men ([Salary.com, 2023](https://www.salary.com/blog/understanding-the-gender-pay-gap/)).

| Group             | Equal Pay Day (Date Women Earn What Men Earned Previous Year) |
|-------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------|
| White Women       | March 9                                                       |
| All Women         | March 24                                                      |
| Mothers           | June 4                                                       |
| Black Women       | August 3                                                     |
| Native American Women | September 8                                               |
| Latinas           | October 21                                                   |

This data highlights the compounded effects of gender and racial discrimination in the labor market.

